        <TR>
          <TD width=55 height=50><IMG height=50 
            src="images/vi2_news_headerL.gif" width=55></TD>
          <TD class=texthead background=images/vi2_news_header_bg.gif 
          height=50 width="100%"><!-- Date --><BR>» 5/31/2002 -- EQ's only non PvP, PvP server <!-- End Date --></TD>
          <TD width=28 height=50><IMG height=50 
            src="images/vi2_news_headerR.gif" width=28></TD></TR>
        <TR>
          <TD width=55>&nbsp;</TD>
          <TD class=textmain colSpan=2>Thought I'd post this in the pretty faint hope that someone over at VI might see it. The players of my server, Tunare, hope to bring to Verant's attention that our server is outrageously overcrowded, both from the point of view of us raid guild folk who, assuming any big mobs are even up, are 100% guaranteed to have to be cutthroat and compete with other players, and from the point of view of anyone who might compare Tunare to other servers. Servers that have one guild that has downed AoW, compared to Tunare's <b>four</b> guilds that have slain him, and race for him, with 2-3 more guilds possibley capable and planning to try if they'd ever get a shot. Other servers with 0 guilds working on slaying Emperor Ssraeshza, compared to Tunare's 4. Servers with one freaking guild doing NToV / Sleepers / Velious royals / Ssra etc, compared to Tunare where non 9th-tier mobs, and im not joking, die within 1-2 hours MAX after spawning, no matter what time of day or night.<br><br>Id like to point out how increadibly unfun this insane amount of competition is, and how players on servers besides Tunare have an opportunity to actually engage in and enjoy the GAME instead of, on a NIGHTLY basis, getting bogged down in races, raid sabatoge (example, our AoW has been trained away from us in the hopes it would despawn by level 1 ogre mules), bickering, general needless antagonism, not to mention the simple fact that we just dont have many big mobs up for us to have fun with.<br><br>Theres a thread going over on <a href='http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showMessageRange?topicID=11109.topic&start=1&stop=20'>the safehouse</a> detailing this; asking people to post a little data concerning the uberguild status of their server. Someone took the time to compile it all together, that data can be found <a href='http://www.frmug.org/~archer/competition.html'>here</a>, showing how top-heavy our server is. Theres another thread on <a href='http://www.fohguild.org/forums/showthread.php?s=&threadid=1384'>FoH's board</a> from a Tunare player on the subject. There is also this thread going on <a href='http://pub13.ezboard.com/ftunaregeneral.showMessageRange?topicID=13483.topic&start=1&stop=20'>Tunare's messageboard</a> about the state of our server.<br><br>Possible solutions? Theres 2. Please for the love of god  consider either splitting Tunare onto a fresh server, or under-utilized server such as Lanys (and assuring guilds that switch that every member will be moved), or decrease the spawn times on the content that the insanely inflated raid guild population of Tunare is after.  <br><br></TD></TR>
        <TR>
          <TD width=55>&nbsp;</TD>
          <TD class=textmain width=55 align="right">-Bloregarr</TD></TR>
        <TR>
          <TD width=55>&nbsp;</TD>
          <TD width=55>&nbsp;</TD></TR>

